headline:"From months to a day: Accelerating fashion photo production with Gemini 3 Pro Image",wr:"AddGlow helps fashion brands and retailers bypass the logistical bottlenecks of traditional photoshoots, providing a retail-specific dashboard specifically designed for enterprise-scale creative production.",Ce:[{name:"Ina Herlihy",role:"Founder and CEO, AddGlow"}],thumbnail:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/addglow/addglow_backgrounds.webp",type:"image",alt:"AddGlow image generation"}}},
{type:"cta",content:{link:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-3-pro-image"}},{type:"text",content:{body:"\n            <p>\n              AddGlow helps fashion brands and retailers bypass the logistical bottlenecks of traditional photoshoots, providing a retail-specific dashboard specifically designed for enterprise-scale creative production. By integrating Gemini 3 Pro into its high-fidelity imaging pipeline, AddGlow brings uncompromising quality to every asset they generate while providing the agility required to meet the demands of the modern retail landscape.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Maintaining production quality for image generation</h2>"},body:"\n            <p>\n              Ensuring accuracy to the garment is the highest priority for AddGlow, which counts popular brands like Elliatt, Mac Duggal, and Alex Apparel as clients. The team found that many AI models would struggle with hallucinations, altering critical details like button styles, necklines, or fabric textures. These inconsistencies erode customer trust, making automated solutions difficult to implement for production-ready work.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"images",content:{items:[{image:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/addglow/addglow_poses.webp",alt:"AddGlow\u2019s pose catalog"},legend:"AddGlow\u2019s pose catalog"}]}},{type:"text",content:{body:"\n            <p>\n              AddGlow addresses this precision gap by leveraging Gemini 3 Pro Image\u2019s multimodal reasoning capabilities and multiple reference images. To ensure accuracy across thousands of unique SKUs, AddGlow developed a sophisticated pipeline that adapts to the physical characteristics of different items and generates high-quality outputs:\n            </p>\n            <ul>\n              <li><b>Automated pre-analysis:</b> The platform uses Gemini Flash-Lite to extract essential metadata from reference inputs, such as garment type, viewing angle, and fabric traits, and structure the prompt accordingly.</li>\n              <li><b>JSON schema grounding:</b> This approach constrains model output to validated, machine-readable data, eliminating the need for manual intervention.</li>\n              <li><b>Human oversight:</b> Every generation includes a human approval step to verify accuracy, ensuring that the final output meets brand-specific creative standards.</li>\n            </ul>"}},
{type:"quote",content:{quote:"Details matter. Without Gemini, we wouldn\u2019t be able to execute on any of our GenAI photo use cases. It\u2019s the only model that meets our quality bar.",author:"\u2014 Ina Herlihy, Founder & CEO of AddGlow"}},{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Accelerating creative output, driving revenue</h2>"},body:"\n            <p>\n              A significant challenge in bringing garments to market is the logistics required for specialized imagery, such as ghost mannequin photography. Traditionally this entailed separate, dedicated sessions where clothing is photographed on a specialized form that is later edited out. The process is expensive, slow, and often requires weeks of retouching.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{body:"\n            <p>\n              AddGlow overcomes these pitfalls by allowing high-volume retailers and luxury fashion brands to generate images from existing photography, significantly reducing the turnaround time for new product launches. Shari Hoenig, VP Ecommerce & Marketing at Alex Apparel Group, notes that AddGlow has \u201cstreamlined the \u2018micro-logistics\u2019 of ecommerce photography by bridging the gap between major campaign shoots and smaller-scale website updates, saving three days of planning and cleanup per cycle.\u201d\n            </p>"}},
{type:"images",content:{items:[{image:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/addglow/addglow_ghostmannequin.webp",alt:"Ghost mannequin images produced from existing Mac Duggal model shots"},legend:"Ghost mannequin images produced from existing Mac Duggal model shots"}]}},{type:"text",content:{body:"\n            <p>\n              Beyond logistical efficiency, brands face the constant need for fresh content to support multiple marketing channels. Previously, brands were often locked into the specific poses captured during a single shoot. AddGlow allows users to focus on capturing core angles, then leverage Gemini Pro Image to generate a wide range of unique poses and backgrounds. \u201cIt gives us more flexibility in presenting products across different channels,\u201d says Emily Greenfield, Head of eCommerce at Mac Duggal. This ability to scale asset creation broadens the opportunity for paid media experimentation, which in turn lifts conversion rates and drives revenue. Nicky Bennett, Head of Ecommerce at ELLIATT, explains, \u201cEven a modest increase in conversion, paired with higher image volume across SKUs, has a meaningful impact on revenue.\u201d\n            </p>"}},
{type:"images",content:{items:[{image:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/addglow/addglow_backgrounds.webp",alt:"How Elliatt replicates an on-location photoshoot"},legend:"How Elliatt replicates an on-location photoshoot"}]}},{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Fine-grained control with Google AI Studio</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              AddGlow found that Google AI Studio provides the tools to maintain a consistent, production-grade aesthetic through controls for aspect ratio and native 4K resolution support. They aim to expand AI-driven offerings to even more complex tasks, such as transforming design illustrations directly into photorealistic images, promising even new ways to scale creative production.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              Read the Gemini API documentation to start building with <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/image-generation">Gemini Pro</a>.\n            </p>'}},
