wr:"Diia.AI deploys conversational agents on Vertex AI to simplify government processes for Ukrainian citizens without compromising data privacy.",Ce:[{name:"Dmytro Ovcharenko",role:"CTO, WINWIN AI Center of Excellence & AI CTO, Ministry of Digital Transformation of Ukraine"}],thumbnail:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/diia/diiaai_thumbnail.jpg",type:"image",alt:"Diia showcase hero"}}},{type:"cta",content:{link:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-flash-latest"}},
{type:"text",content:{body:"\n          <p>\n            Diia is an online platform and app developed by the Ministry of Digital Transformation of Ukraine, offering over 23 million citizens digital access to 33 essential government documents\u2014including ID cards, driver's licenses, and passports\u2014and more than 150 services covering everything from traffic tickets to taxes. The platform\u2019s next phase is an AI-powered transformation: Diia.AI, an agent designed to proactively offer services and eliminate bureaucracy.\n          </p>\n          <p>\n            The team chose Gemini 2.0 Flash to build it due to its superior cost-efficiency and performance, and to host it via Vertex AI for maximum data security.\n          </p>"}},
{type:"video",content:{video:{sources:[{url:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/diia/diiaai_demo.mp4",type:"video/mp4"}],legend:"The Diia.AI chatbot interface shows a user requesting their insurance history and ordering an official income statement through an AI assistant."}}},{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Making government services accessible to over 23 million Ukrainian citizens</h2>"},body:"\n            <p>\n              Diia helps make government services accessible to everyone, regardless of technical literacy or familiarity with complex processes. Dmytro Ovcharenko, CTO at the WINWIN AI Center of Excellence and AI CTO at the Ministry of Digital Transformation of Ukraine, noted, \u201cOur goal is to make Diia accessible and useful to everyone, from students to entrepreneurs to pensioners.\u201d Integrating agentic AI into the platform would aid citizens in navigating both Diia and complex government forms and processes.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              Supporting a model of this magnitude in-house, however, was not feasible. After evaluating several cloud-based options, the team determined that Gemini 2.0 Flash would be the ideal solution for performance, scalability, and cost. The model needed to not only excel in conversational Ukrainian but also understand and generate complex legal and administrative phrasing. To ensure accuracy, it used Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) to access a constantly updated, validated knowledge base built from official Diia sources.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"quote",content:{quote:"Other high-performance, API-based models were financially prohibitive. Gemini 2.0 Flash showed really great results, delivering the speed and intelligence we needed at a cost that made the project viable.",author:"- Dmytro Ovcharenko<br><br>CTO at the WINWIN AI Center of Excellence and AI CTO at the Ministry of Digital Transformation of Ukraine"}},{type:"text",content:{body:"\n            <p>\n              Within the first day of its launch, over 4,000 unique users engaged with Diia.AI, sending over 20,000 messages. Nearly a quarter of the income certificates delivered that day\u2014a highly requested document\u2014were processed through conversations with the AI assistant. Within two weeks, over 20,000 users had sent 64,000 messages, indicating rapid platform adoption.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Creating an \u201cairlock\u201d: government-grade data security with Vertex AI</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              Given the agent would be handling Personally Identifiable Information (PII), security and privacy was top priority. Hosting the model on Google\u2019s <a href="https://cloud.google.com/products/agent-builder?hl=en">Vertex AI</a> platform delivered the necessary government-grade security. \u201cWe absolutely could not use any service that would train its models on our users\' queries,\u201d said Ovcharenko, adding, \u201cThe assurance that our data would not be used for training was something that other solutions could not offer with the same level of confidence.\u201d</p><p>The team needed to create an \u201cairlock\u201d between the user\u2019s data and the AI model so the model could work without ever processing raw PII. To handle questions involving PII, they created a unique backend architecture on <a href="https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/">FastAPI</a> and Python, using <a href="https://www.langchain.com/langgraph">LangGraph</a> for orchestration.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"video",content:{video:{sources:[{url:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/diia/diiaai_graph.mp4",type:"video/mp4"}],legend:"The diagram shows how PII stays private in an \u201cairlock\u201d system. Once a user initiates a request, it is processed via an Model Context Protocol (MCP), which retrieves data from the state registries. A proprietary PIIManager then acts as an output adapter on top of MCP, ensuring that all responses remain anonymized. Gemini 2.0 Flash then receives this anonymized data and generates a natural response. This response is sent back to the backend, where it is \u201crehydrated\u201d with the original PII before being delivered to the user."}}},
{type:"text",content:{body:"\n            <p>\n              Ovcharenko noted that Gemini helped deliver a service that was previously \u201cimpossible to automate\u201d. Response times come in under the Ministry\u2019s strict sub-2-second Time to First Token (TTFT) target to ensure Diia.AI feels naturally responsive and conversational. The process capitalized on the Gemini model\u2019s speed and excellent Ukrainian understanding to create a highly secure experience without ever coming into contact with raw PII.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Broadening features beyond chat</h2>"},body:"\n            <p>\n              The team plans to further refine Diia.AI and integrate it into Diia\u2019s mobile app to further broaden its accessibility. They also have plans to expand the amount of services Diia.AI can offer and introduce new features built with Gemini beyond the chat agent. \u201cThis is just the beginning,\u201d said Dmytro. \u201cWe're not just building an app; we\u2019re building the future of public service.\u201d\n            </p>"}},
