content:{date:"Dec 30, 2025",headline:"Assort Health improves healthcare access by automating millions of patient calls with Gemini 2.5 Flash",wr:"Assort Health's AI agents use Gemini 2.5 Flash to handle a wide range of patient interactions, leading to lower wait times and increased appointment bookings.",Ce:[{name:"Jon Wang",role:"Founder and Co-CEO, Assort Health"},{name:"Jeffery Liu",role:"Founder and Co-CEO, Assort Health"},{name:"Sean Muirhead",role:"Agent Engineering Lead, Assort Health"},{name:"Vishal Dharmadhikari",
role:"Product Solutions Engineer"}],thumbnail:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/Assort_Health_hero.jpg",type:"image",alt:"Assort Health showcase hero"}}},{type:"stats",content:{stats:[{value:"5%",description:"Increase in total number of appointments booked"},{value:"89%",description:"Reduction in patient wait times"},{value:"50M+",description:"Interactions averaging a 4.3 / 5 CSAT score"}]}},{type:"cta",content:{link:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-flash-latest"}},
{type:"text",content:{body:"\n            <p>\n              Imagine having 24/7 access to your healthcare provider. Assort Health is doing just that by revolutionizing patient access and operational efficiency in healthcare with its specialty-trained agentic AI contact center that handles a range of patient interactions.\n            </p>"}},{type:"video",content:{video:{sources:[{url:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/assort/assorthealth_diagram.mp4",type:"video/mp4"}],legend:"Simplified visualization for illustrative purposes."}}},
{type:"text",content:{body:"\n            <p>\n              Historically, automating healthcare workflows has been one of the industry\u2019s toughest challenges, especially for specialty-specific tasks that require a deep understanding of the domain. Assort Health has cracked the code on that complexity, leveraging data across thousands of providers and 55 million interactions.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              Agentic state machines work together to navigate complex appointment logic, payer information, and other requirements unique to each specialty. This efficiency has led to a 5% increase in the number of appointments booked while decreasing operational costs by 48% for customers.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Implementing Gemini 2.5 Flash for speed and context</h2>"},body:"\n            <p>\n              Assort Health\u2019s platform goes far beyond appointment scheduling to handle the complexities of healthcare:\n            </p>\n              <ul>\n                <li><b>Insurance capture:</b> Accurately recording and verifying insurance information</li>\n                <li><b>Refill requests:</b> Processing medication refill requests efficiently</li>\n                <li><b>Care gap closures:</b> Running proactive campaigns to mitigate surges in demand for care like flu season, closing care gaps and improving population health</li>\n              </ul>\n            <p>\n              The system must accurately account for patient appointment history, chief complaints, insurance details, and medical specialty-specific rules.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              Gemini 2.5 Flash enables Assort Health to manage these complex, latency-sensitive workflows. AI agents can handle a high volume of interactions while maintaining the necessary speed and contextual understanding to ensure a seamless experience. The results are significant: 89% shorter wait times, 81% lower call abandonment rate, and a customer satisfaction (CSAT) score of 4.3/5 from over 50 million patient-agent interactions.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Scaling healthcare accessibility</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              Assort Health demonstrates how AI agents can help scale patient access in healthcare. The platform is projected to handle over 100 million interactions by the end of the year and will continue development of specialty-specific AI agents to expand inbound and outbound communications.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              To start building applications with Gemini models, explore our <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs">API documentation</a>.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"related_cases",content:{qf:["raindrop","passionfroot","calcam"]}}]},{title:"CompScience",We:"CompScience analyzes thousands of hours of video footage to improve industrial worksite safety",slug:"compscience",Af:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-flash-latest",fia:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-pro-latest",thumbnail:{url:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/compScience/CompScience_thumbnail.jpg",alt:"CompScience showcase preview"},
te:["Gemini 2.5 Pro","Gemini 2.5 Flash"],modules:[{type:"hero",content:{date:"Jan 7, 2025",headline:"CompScience improves industrial worksite safety with on-demand image and video analysis",wr:"CompScience uses Gemini 2.5 Pro and 2.5 Flash to analyze worksite footage and mitigate realtime hazards. Through their Safe Work Plan, Safety Pulse, and Safety Search products, they scale expert knowledge to help workers stay safe on the job.",Ce:[{name:"Dan Walton",role:"Principal Engineer, CompScience"},
{name:"Vishal Dharmadhikari",role:"Product Solutions Engineer"}],thumbnail:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/compScience/CompScience_hero.jpg",type:"image",alt:"CompScience showcase hero"}}},{type:"stats",content:{stats:[{value:"400%",description:"Adoption of Safe Work Plan vs. standard techniques"},{value:"15K+",description:"Hours of video footage processed"},{value:"60",description:"Detailed risk reports deployed to industry"}]}},{type:"cta",content:{link:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-flash-latest"}},
{type:"text",content:{body:"\n            <p>\n              CompScience is on a mission to eliminate workplace accidents by using AI to provide Safe Work Plans, real-time alerts, and comprehensive safety reports derived from worksite video footage. Partnering with professional risk experts like the National Safety Council, CompScience serves over 100 industrial customers across a variety of sectors, helping them identify risks before they become injuries.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              The core challenge for CompScience is the sheer volume of data. Industrial worksites generate hundreds of hours of video every day. Manually reviewing this footage for potential hazards is impossible at scale. To turn this massive unstructured dataset into concise, actionable safety information, CompScience turned to the Gemini API.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Scaling expert safety knowledge with Gemini 2.5 Pro</h2>"},body:"\n            <p>\n              CompScience utilizes Gemini 2.5 Pro to build their Safe Work Plan application. When maintenance workers encounter unplanned work in a factory, they can use their cellphones to take photos of the situation.\n            </p>"}},{type:"images",content:{items:[{image:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/compScience/CompScience_inline_01.jpg",alt:"Phone screen allowing users to input job details to conduct a quick Risk Prediction."},
legend:"Workers can submit photos from job sites to generate a Safe Work Plan detailing hazards and proposed safeguards."}]}},{type:"text",content:{body:"\n            <p>\n              2.5 Pro processes these images, reasons through complex safety assessment rubrics, and provides expert-informed advice and guidance. These recommendations can then be saved as standard safe company procedures, effectively digitizing and scaling expert safety knowledge.\n            </p>"}},{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Processing over 15 thousand hours of video with Gemini 2.5 Flash</h2>"},
body:"\n            <p>\n              Beyond static images, CompScience needs to process continuous video streams for their Safety Pulse and Safety Search products. They utilize Gemini 2.5 Flash to periodically assess worksite cameras for immediate issues and to rapidly search through hundreds of hours of archived video in minutes to generate impact reports.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              According to Daniel Walton, Principal Engineer at CompScience, 2.5 Flash\u2019s native video processing capabilities are a key differentiator, noting that \u201cvideo processing just isn\u2019t available\u201d at the same level with other AI providers they tested. To manage the high throughput of video data, CompScience leverages the Files API, using multiple threads to upload video and generate insights efficiently.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              A recent development for CompScience is utilizing Gemini 2.5 Flash\u2019s ability to generate bounding boxes around identified hazards within continuous video or images. This visual grounding allows them to help identify unsafe behaviors or conditions in their reports, a feature Walton notes is \u201conly possible with Gemini 2.5 Flash\u201d for their specific use case.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"images",content:{items:[{image:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/compScience/CompScience_inline_02.jpg",alt:'Two screenshots of the CompScience SafetyPulse interface. The left screen shows a video feed from a construction site with a green bounding box around a crane, alongside an "Alert" log identifying a suspended load hazard. A "Take Action" pop-up menu allows users to select corrective measures. The right screen displays a "Safety Overview" dashboard with camera activity thumbnails, alert summaries, and a generated report listing potential safety hazards and recommendations for improvement.'},
legend:"Gemini 2.5 Flash processes job site security photos for safety managers to review, then generates actionable daily reports."}]}},{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Proactively improving safety and mitigating hazards</h2>"},body:"\n            <p>\n              By integrating Gemini models, CompScience currently delivers video-driven safety reports to hundreds of customers. The effectiveness of their AI-driven approach has led the National Safety Council to include the CompScience Safe Work Plan system for their own members, scaling these safety benefits to a broader industrial audience.\n            </p>"}},
