te:["Gemini 3 Flash"],modules:[{type:"hero",content:{date:"DEC 17, 2025",headline:"Delivering real-time deepfake intelligence with Gemini 3 Flash",Ce:[{name:"Sarah Dolen",role:"AI Futures Fund"},{name:"Zohaib Ahmed",role:"Founder & CEO, Resemble AI"},{name:"Vishal Dharmadhikari",role:"Developer Solutions Engineer"}],thumbnail:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/resemble_ai/resemble_ai_hero.jpg",type:"image",alt:"Shopify showcase hero"}}},{type:"cta",content:{link:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-3-flash-preview"}},
{type:"text",content:{body:'\n            <p>\n              <a href="http://resemble.ai">Resemble AI</a> is a leader in generative voice and deepfake detection. As deepfakes become more sophisticated, enterprise clients in regulated industries need more than a binary "Real" or "Fake" label\u2014they need to understand why content is flagged, instantly.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              To bridge the gap between technical forensics and human understanding, Resemble AI integrated <a href="http://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models#gemini-3.0-flash">Gemini 3 Flash</a> into "Resemble Intelligence," a system that turns complex detection data into natural language explanations without sacrificing real-time performance.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Speed is everything: from pixel-level analysis to high-level reasoning</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              Whether it\'s a consumer trying to verify a viral video or a bank\'s voice agent authenticating a caller, the race against fraudulent content happens in a matter of seconds. Latency can break the flow of critical interactions. Traditionally, detection models output technical heatmaps or probability scores that, while accurate, fail to answer the user\'s most pressing question: "Why is this suspicious?"\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              To provide this essential layer of explainability in near real-time, Resemble AI built a seamless pipeline pairing their proprietary <a href="https://www.resemble.ai/detect-3b-omni">DETECT-3B Omni</a> model to identify specific manipulation artifacts with Gemini 3 Flash to generate context-rich explanations. This integration achieves 4x faster multimodal analysis over 2.5 Pro, analyzing raw technical outputs without slowing down critical workflows.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"video",content:{video:{Sfa:!0,title:"Sequences shortened",sources:[{url:"https://ai.google.dev/static/showcase/resembleai/videos/resembleai_gemini_demo.mp4",type:"video/mp4"}]}}},{type:"text",content:{body:'\n            <p>\n              Resemble AI also pairs Gemini 3 Flash with their latest open-source text-to-speech model, <a href="https://www.resemble.ai/chatterbox/">Chatterbox</a>, for interactive voice AI agents with sub-second response times.             </p>'}},{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Grounded intelligence: prioritizing forensic integrity</h2>"},
body:'\n            <p>\n              Resemble AI leverages the advanced reasoning of Gemini 3 Flash to achieve a higher standard of forensic integrity. The system generates 25% fewer fabricated artifacts than previous iterations, ensuring that every automated explanation remains strictly grounded in forensic data.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              This accuracy is critical for businesses that require compliance with regulatory requirements. To help enterprises navigate global transparency mandates like the EU AI Act, Resemble AI uses Gemini 3 Flash to help verify proprietary watermarks and provide clear, actionable intelligence.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              For verified voice agents, detection happens in real time. If a call is flagged, Gemini 3 Flash instantly generates a summary explaining the specific risk factors involved. This allows for a smooth "human handoff," ensuring the operator takes over with full context rather than flying blind.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"text",content:{body:'\n            <p>\n              Resemble AI\u2019s implementation demonstrates that safety and speed do not have to be a trade-off. By adding a layer of explainability to their detection reports, they help provide enterprises with the intelligence needed to act on deepfakes, not just detect them.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              To start building with Gemini models, read our <a href="https://ai.google.dev/docs">API documentation</a> or try out the model in <a href="https://aistudio.google.com/">Google AI Studio</a>.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"related_cases",content:{qf:["ava","cartwheel","optimalai"]}}]},{title:"InstaLILY",We:"InstaLILY uses Gemini 3 and Gemma to build vertical AI agents with domain-specific knowledge.",slug:"instalily",Af:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-3.1-pro-preview",thumbnail:{url:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/Instality_thumbnail.jpg",alt:"Instalily showcase preview"},te:["Gemini 3 Pro","Gemma"],modules:[{type:"hero",content:{date:"December 15, 2025",headline:"InstaLILY: Giving companies the power of two AIs in one system",
Ce:[{name:"Amit Shah",role:"Co-Founder & CEO, InstaLILY"},{name:"Matt Ridenour",role:"Head of Startups, Google DeepMind"}],thumbnail:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/instalily/Instalily_hero.jpg",type:"image",alt:"Instalily showcase hero"}}},{type:"stats",content:{stats:[{value:"60%",description:"reduction in training time"},{value:"10%",description:"revenue uplift as a result of faster quote requests"},{value:"3",description:"minute case routing time (compared to 15 minutes previously)"}]}},
{type:"cta",content:{link:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-3.1-pro-preview"}},{type:"text",content:{body:'\n            <p>\n              <a href="https://instalily.ai/">InstaLILY</a> is transforming how big businesses work by creating specialized AI teammates that are experts in their field. Instead of one-size-fits-all AI, InstaLILY builds "vertical AI agents" that understand the specific needs of sales, service, and operations at an enterprise level.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              By pairing the reasoning capability of <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models#gemini-3.0-pro">Gemini 3 Pro</a> with domain-specific <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemma/docs">Gemma</a> models, InstaLILY gives companies the power of two AIs in one system.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>The power of two: Gemini 3 for smart thinking, Gemma for fast action</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              InstaLILY uses a unique "hybrid" system that combines two powerful Google AI models to get the best of both worlds:\n            </p>\n              <ul>\n                <li><b>Gemini 3 Pro for deep reasoning:</b> This is the technical brains of the operation. The model handles complex reasoning, interpreting difficult situations, validating steps, and making sure everything aligns with the company\'s internal rules and procedures (stored in an "enterprise memory" called InstaBrain\u2122).</li>\n                <li><b>Gemma-based Small Language Models (SLMs) for vertical efficiency:</b> These are the specialist agents. Gemma models provide fine-tuned performance for specific, domain-related tasks, such as processing long audio recordings or classifying different types of customer requests.</li>\n              </ul>'}},
{type:"video",content:{video:{title:"Training pipeline",sources:[{url:"https://ai.google.dev/static/images/showcase/instalily/instalily_pipeline.mp4",type:"video/mp4"}]}}},{type:"text",content:{body:"\n            <p>\n              This partnership, accelerated by Google's custom TPU v5e chips, helps to ensure the system is both incredibly smart and incredibly fast, delivering high-level performance right away.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              InstaLILY produces transformative solutions for different use cases through a uniform systems architecture rather than custom code. Each deployment relies on the same connector layer for structured access to operational systems, the same editable enterprise-memory substrate (InstaBrain\u2122) that generates a vertical SLM, and the same orchestrated agent layer where execution is standardized, controlled, and enterprise-grade.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>1. Real-time field intelligence for sales and service teams</h2>"},body:"\n            <p>\n              Field technicians and sales reps, especially new hires, struggle with multi-hour, complex visits. They have to manually consult engineering guides, follow diagnostic steps, and ensure compliance with safety and pricing rules, which leads to delays and inconsistent service. Using InstaLILY, training time was shortened from 120 days to just over a month.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              The agent uses Gemma to process audio from the visit while Gemini 3 acts as a real-time fact checker that validates every inspection step and confirms compliance with all procedures. Reviews of multi-hour appointments now take just 10 minutes for managers, and scores for adherence to safety and standard operating procedures have increased from 50% to 90%.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>2. Autonomous case routing for logistics and shipping operations</h2>"},body:"\n            <p>\n              Companies manually sort tens of thousands of logistics cases (e.g., shipping issues, changes) every month using outdated systems and complicated rulebooks.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              InstaLILY agents reduce bottlenecks and long queues by using Gemma to quickly identify the case type and extract key details. At the same time, Gemini interprets complex routing logic and automatically resolves exceptions. By removing slow, sequential steps, the system reduces case processing times from 15 minutes to three minutes.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>3. Quote acceleration for industrial distributors and suppliers</h2>"},body:"\n            <p>\n              Parts suppliers and industrial distributors receive quote requests through messy, unstructured channels including emails, free-text inquiries, and PDFs. Manually sorting, interpreting, and responding to these requests takes 5-6 days, often leading to lost sales opportunities.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              InstaLILY uses Gemini 3 Pro to interpret the customer's objective from the unstructured documents and resolves confusing product identifiers. Gemma classifies the request type and automatically drafts a response. Integrated with inventory and ERP systems, the agents generate a full quote in minutes. Faster turnarounds times contributed to an approximately 10% uplift revenue.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"quote",content:{quote:"Enterprises do not need generic copilots. They need AI agents that understand their industry, follow their rules and operate at the speed their workflows demand. Gemini 3 and Gemma give us the foundation to build vertical agents that perform with the clarity, consistency and reliability that mission-critical enterprise teams expect on day one.",author:"\u2014 Amit Shah, CEO & Co-Founder, InstaLILY AI"}},{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>A new era of enterprise AI</h2>"},
body:'\n            <p>\n              By combining the sophisticated reasoning power of Gemini 3 Pro with the vertical-specific speed of Gemma, InstaLILY is delivering an enterprise architecture capable of true high-level performance, bringing massive transformation to field service, logistics, and distribution.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              To start building with Gemini and Gemma models, visit <a href="https://aistudio.google.com/">Google AI Studio</a> and read our <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs">API documentation</a>.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"related_cases",content:{qf:["resembleai"]}}]},{title:"Shopify",We:"Discover how Shopify built Sidekick using Gemini 2.5 Flash and Live API. Learn how this multimodal AI assistant helps merchants scale with real-time voice and video support.",slug:"shopify",Af:"https://aistudio.google.com/live",thumbnail:{url:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/shopify/shopify_featured.jpg",alt:"Shopify showcase preview"},te:["Gemini 2.5 Flash"],modules:[{type:"hero",content:{date:"DEC 12, 2025",
headline:"Shopify helps merchants win with Sidekick, a multimodal AI assistant powered by the Live API",Ce:[{name:"David Wurtz",role:"VP of Product, Shopify"}],thumbnail:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/shopify/shopify_hero.jpg",type:"image",alt:"Shopify showcase hero"}}},{type:"cta",content:{link:"https://aistudio.google.com/live"}},{type:"text",content:{body:'\n            <p>\n              <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.shopify.mobile">Shopify</a> is the leading global commerce platform, providing the essential infrastructure needed to start, scale, and market a retail business of any size. In an ongoing effort to improve the experience for its merchants, the Shopify team wanted to offer a personalized, in-depth assistant to help millions of businesses start and scale across more than 175 countries.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              To achieve this they developed Sidekick, an AI assistant designed to partner with merchants on everything from design to analytics. By integrating voice and video processing through the <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/live">Live API</a>, Sidekick is an interactive, capable commerce assistant that can help in real-time, often during merchants\u2019 most challenging periods.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Sidekick: a capable commerce assistant to help merchants work efficiently</h2>"},body:"\n            <p>\n              The Shopify team wanted Sidekick to seamlessly connect commerce knowledge to a merchant\u2019s unique needs. In voice mode, Sidekick can help merchants navigate the Shopify admin, search shop resources, pull analytics on their store performance, and other actions via tools. It can even help troubleshoot issues outside of the admin through the screen sharing feature.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"video",content:{video:{Sfa:!0,title:"Sidekick voice demo",sources:[{url:"https://ai.google.dev/static/showcase/shopify/videos/SidekickVoiceDemo.mp4",type:"video/mp4"}]}}},{type:"text",content:{body:"\n            <p>\n              By pairing complex reasoning with voice-powered interactions, Sidekick provides robust support away from a desk\u2014critical for merchants that are often on the go, meeting in a warehouse, or working with their hands.\n            </p>"}},{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Enabling conversational assistance with the Live API</h2>"},
body:"\n            <p>\n              The Sidekick team used Gemini 2.5 Flash Native Audio and the Live API to process audio and output realistic-sounding speech with low latency. Conversations had to feel responsive, as disruptions in conversational flow could ruin the user experience and dissuade use. The team adjusted cues, tone, and turn-taking\u2014when the bot should interrupt and how eager it should be to speak\u2014to make interactions feel more natural.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              These voice and video capabilities helped counter the expectation of a simple chatbot, avoiding the pitfalls of many AI assistants. \u201cUsers often forget they\u2019re talking to AI within a minute of using Sidekick, and in some cases have thanked the bot after a long chat,\u201d said David Wurtz, VP of Product.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Building an integrated platform to scale productivity</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              Making an AI assistant that felt capable and conversational was an iterative task. The Shopify team went from prototyping with Gemini models in <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/live">Google AI Studio</a> to testing the feature with real users on <a href="https://console.cloud.google.com/vertex-ai/studio/multimodal-live">Vertex AI</a> in just three weeks.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              From marketing to operations, the team is always looking to help merchants scale their business with their <a href="https://www.shopify.com/magic">integrated platform</a>. Wurtz says, \u201cThis is an exciting time to be an entrepreneur. New AI capabilities like those offered through Gemini empower our merchants to win.\u201d\n            </p>'}},
{type:"related_cases",content:{qf:["ava","volley-2","raindrop"]}}]},{title:"Ava",We:"Explore how Ava helps families manage their household using Gemini 2.5 Flash models and the Live API for agentic workflows.",slug:"ava",Af:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-flash-latest",thumbnail:{url:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/ava/Ava_thumbnail.jpg",alt:"Ava showcase preview"},te:["Gemini 2.5 Flash"],modules:[{type:"hero",content:{date:"DEC 12, 2025",headline:"Ava: Building agentic workflows with Gemini 2.5 Flash and the Live API",
Ce:[{name:"Joe Alicata",role:"Co-founder & CTO Ava"},{name:"Vishal Dharmadhikari",role:"Developer Solutions Engineer"}],thumbnail:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/ava/Ava_hero.jpg",type:"image",alt:"Ava showcase hero"}}},{type:"cta",content:{link:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-flash-latest"}},{type:"text",content:{body:'\n            <p>\n              <a href="https://hiava.app/?utm_source=google&utm_medium=blog&utm_campaign=spotlight">Ava</a> is an \u201cAI-powered family operating system\u201d designed to manage the logistics of family life by anticipating needs and automating tasks.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              The information parents manage is rarely structured; it arrives via inconsistent school emails, screenshots of flyers, PDF attachments, lengthy WhatsApp threads, and voice notes. Ava must understand the context and seamlessly interact with external services.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              To handle the messy, unstructured inputs of the real world, the Ava team implemented a tiered architecture using <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models#gemini-2.5-flash">Gemini 2.5 Flash models</a> for different stages of their agentic pipeline and the <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/live">Live API</a> to provide a conversational interface.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"images",content:{items:[{image:{src:"https://ai.google.dev/static/showcase/ava/images/ava-showcase.jpg",alt:"Ava showcase"}}]}},{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Optimizing performance and efficiency</h2>"},body:"\n            <p>\n              Incoming requests first encounter a lightweight agent router to make the user experience feel responsive. This router acts as the triage system, classifying the priority of the input, extracting key slots (who, when, where), and deciding which specialized tool or subsequent model is required.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              According to Joe Alicata, co-founder and CTO of Ava, \u201cGemini 2.5 Flash-Lite shines for ultra-lightweight checks,\u201d handling intent detection and short-form summarization while delivering sub-second responses.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Handling complex planning and execution</h2>"},body:"\n            <p>\n              Once intent is established, tasks often require deeper reasoning. For example, parsing a school calendar, normalizing inconsistent dates, and proposing the correct event requires nuanced understanding. Gemini 2.5 Flash enables Ava to serve as a capable \u201chousehold COO\u201d by meeting exacting technical requirements:\n            </p>\n              <ul>\n                <li><strong>Multimodal understanding</strong>: Processing text, images, and audio in a single pass</li>\n                <li><strong>Increased accuracy under ambiguity</strong>: Correctly interpreting inconsistent school communications</li>\n                <li><strong>Reliable function calling</strong>: Ensuring that actions, such as calling Gmail and the Calendar API, use structured and trustworthy data</li>\n              </ul>\n            <p>\n              Families can manage their household tasks entirely through voice interactions enabled by the Live API. Alicata noted they had a \u201chard requirement around native audio\u201d so Ava feels like a natural tool to leverage.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"video",content:{video:{Sfa:!0,title:"Ava voice demo",sources:[{url:"https://ai.google.dev/static/showcase/ava/videos/ava_video.mp4",type:"video/mp4"}]}}},{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>A mature approach to building agentic systems</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              The team used Google AI Studio extensively during development to rapidly iterate on prompts and tool schemas as well as A/B test candidate models, shortening the idea-to-test loop from days to hours.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              The results demonstrated the efficacy of their multi-model approach. They observed higher first-pass accuracy on noisy inputs like email threads and photos of flyers. During its alpha sprint, 80% of Ava users were daily active users, and thousands of triaged events were approved and added to calendars.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              By using highly-efficient models for fast reads and reserving more resource-intensive models for complex analysis, agentic systems can work at the speed of real life.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              To explore how Gemini models and the Live API can streamline agentic workflows, review our <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs">API documentation</a>.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"related_cases",content:{qf:["shopify","volley-2","raindrop"]}}]},{title:"Toongether",We:"toongether democratizes visual storytelling with Gemini 2.5 Flash Image. Explore how they help users overcome drawing barriers to create consistent, high-quality comics.",slug:"toongether",Af:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-flash-latest",thumbnail:{url:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/toongether/Toongether_thumbnail.jpg",alt:"Toongether showcase preview"},te:["Gemini 2.5 Flash Image"],
modules:[{type:"hero",content:{date:"DEC 12, 2025",headline:"Toongether maintains art style consistency using Gemini 2.5 Flash Image",Ce:[{name:"Samir Nasser Eddine",role:"Co-founder of toongether"},{name:"Guillaume Vernade",role:"DeepMind Senior Developer Advocate"}],thumbnail:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/Toongether_hero.jpg",type:"image",alt:"Toongether showcase hero"}}},{type:"cta",content:{link:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-flash-latest"}},{type:"text",
content:{body:"\n            <p>\n              The rise of generative AI has opened new frontiers for creative expression, allowing developers to build tools that turn casual users into artists. However, for sequential art like comics, the challenge isn't just generating a single good image\u2014it\u2019s generating consistent characters, styles, and narratives across dozens of panels.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              toongether, the company behind the webcomics app, is tackling this challenge head-on. Their mission is to democratize visual storytelling, providing a platform where casual users can not only read but also create and share their own comics directly from their mobile devices. By integrating Gemini 2.5 Flash Image into their creation pipeline, they are helping users overcome the technical hurdles of drawing, enabling a new community of storytellers to co-create.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Achieving consistency at scale</h2>"},body:"\n            <p>\n              Creating a comic demands rigorous consistency. Characters must remain recognizable across different poses, outfits, and facial expressions, all while adhering to a unified art style.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              Initially, the toongether team relied on a complex stack involving a fine-tuned Stable Diffusion XL model enhanced with tools like ControlNet and IPAdapters. While this delivered qualitative results, it struggled with latency and flexibility\u2014major bottlenecks for mobile builders. Generating a single image took between 20 and 30 seconds, which is too slow for a seamless user experience. Furthermore, adding support for new poses or drawing styles required significant engineering effort, limiting their ability to iterate quickly.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Orchestrating complex pipelines with Gemini</h2>"},body:"\n            <p>\n              To overcome these bottlenecks, toongether migrated their core image generation pipeline to the Gemini API. They chose Gemini 2.5 Flash Image\u2014also known affectionately as \u201cNano Banana\u201d for its speed and agility\u2014which offered the superior editing and instruction-following capabilities needed to handle complex, multi-step generation tasks.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              The transition dramatically accelerated their development velocity, with the team moving from a prototype to a full production implementation in just two weeks.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              To maintain character consistency while allowing for user customization, toongether leveraged Gemini 2.5 Flash Image to build a sophisticated multi-stage pipeline:\n            </p>\n              <ul>\n                <li>\n                  <b>Style analysis & reference generation:</b> When a user creates a new character, the app provides the model with a curated list of reference characters to analyze the desired style. Based on a simple text description, the model generates a \u201cneutral pose\u201d reference image for this new original character.\n                </li>\n                <li>\n                  <b>Asset packs & pose generation:</b> To put that character into a story, toongether uses \u201casset packs\u201d\u2014grouped lists of descriptions for desired poses and use cases. By utilizing an instruction prompt along with the neutral reference image, they can instruct Gemini 2.5 Flash Image to generate specific scenarios without losing the character's visual identity.\n                </li>\n                <li>\n                  <b>Scene composition:</b> For backgrounds and other elements, the team provides reference images to infer the correct art style, ensuring cohesive panels.\n                </li>\n              </ul>\n            </p>"}},
{type:"images",content:{items:[{image:{src:"https://ai.google.dev/static/showcase/toongether/images/Toongether_Case Study_Image.jpg",alt:"Toongether showcase image"}}]}},{type:"text",content:{body:"\n            <p>\n              \u201cBy leveraging the advanced editing and instruction capabilities of Gemini 2.5 Flash Image, we were able to support all our use cases,\u201d explains Samir Nasser Eddine, co-founder of toongether. \u201cIt\u2019s now an essential part of our image generation pipelines.\u201d\n            </p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>What\u2019s next for toongether</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              With their foundational elements in place, the toongether team is looking toward advanced narrative features previously considered too resource-intensive. They plan to use Gemini models to support complex interactions between multiple characters within a single panel and to introduce a wider variety of drawing styles.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              toongether\u2019s journey highlights how the Gemini API helps the next cohort of builders move beyond managing complex model stacks to building sophisticated, consistent creative tools that scale to casual users.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              To start building your own creative applications with Gemini models, read our <a href="https://ai.google.dev/docs">API documentation</a>.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"related_cases",content:{qf:["cartwheel","toonsutra-2","synthesia"]}}]},{title:"HubX",We:"By leveraging Nano Banana\u2019s native multimodality for its ReShoot app, HubX enables conversational editing and improves efficiency by consolidating workflows that previously required multiple models.",slug:"hubx",Af:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-2.5-flash-image",thumbnail:{url:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/HubX_thumbnail.jpg",alt:"HubX showcase preview"},
te:["Gemini 2.5 Flash Image"],modules:[{type:"hero",content:{date:"November 7, 2025",headline:"HubX integrates Gemini 2.5 Flash Image for low-latency, contextual photo editing",wr:"By leveraging Nano Banana\u2019s native multimodality for its ReShoot app, HubX enables conversational editing and improves efficiency by consolidating workflows that previously required multiple models.",Ce:[{name:"Sertac \u00c7\u0131nar",role:"Sr. Product Manager HubX"},{name:"Vishal Dharmadhikari",role:"Product Solutions Engineer"}],
thumbnail:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/HubX_hero.jpg",type:"image",alt:"HubX showcase hero"}}},{type:"stats",content:{stats:[{value:"40%",description:"Reduction in latency"}]}},{type:"cta",content:{link:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-2.5-flash-image"}},{type:"text",content:{body:'<p>\n              <a href="https://hubx.co/">HubX</a> is a global technology hub serving over 300 million users across its portfolio of mobile applications. When developing their latest app, ReShoot, they aimed to democratize professional-level photo editing using generative AI. By leveraging the Gemini API, the team achieved a remarkable development velocity, taking the project from the start of MVP development to a live iOS launch in just two weeks. Shortly after, ReShoot claimed the #1 rank in the US Graphics & Design category on the App Store.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              The app\u2019s goal is to allow users to alter the scene or style of a photo without losing the natural look and identity of the original subject. For developers, delivering this level of complex, multimodal reasoning within the stringent low-latency requirements of a mobile experience presents a significant architectural challenge. To address this, HubX utilized the Gemini API to build a sophisticated photo editing pipeline that balances high-fidelity contextual understanding with exceptional inference speed.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"images",content:{items:[{image:{src:"https://ai.google.dev/static/showcase/hubx/images/hubx_01.jpg",alt:"HubX"}}]}},{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>High-fidelity editing with Nano Banana</h2>"},body:"<p>\n              To construct the reasoning engine behind ReShoot, HubX worked with the Google team to integrate <b>Gemini 2.5 Flash Image</b> \u2014also known as <b>Nano Banana</b>.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              A primary technical challenge in image-to-image generation is maintaining subject identity while interpreting complex scene requests. Unlike traditional pipelines that often require chaining separate models for text reasoning and image synthesis, Gemini 2.5 Flash Image is natively multimodal. It processes text prompts and image inputs in a single, unified step.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              This architecture allows ReShoot to perform conversational editing (image + text-to-image) with high adherence to user prompts while preserving the core identity and context of the uploaded photos. Compared to alternatives tested, HubX found that the Gemini model offered superior visual comprehension and multimodal consistency.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Reducing app latency by 40%</h2>"},body:"<p>\n              While high-fidelity generation is requisite, mobile users expect near-instant results. Any friction in the creative process can lead to engagement loss.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              By standardizing on Gemini 2.5 Flash Image, HubX reduced the average response time for updating and manipulating images by nearly 40%. This critical reduction in latency transforms the user experience from a passive waiting state to a fluid creative process, which is essential for retention in consumer mobile apps.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"video",content:{video:{title:"HubX",sources:[{url:"https://ai.google.dev/static/showcase/hubx/video/hubx_1.mp4",type:"video/mp4"}]}}},{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Streamlining development workflows</h2>"},body:'<p>\n              Beyond immediate performance gains, integrating the Gemini API significantly simplified the HubX development architecture. The team utilizes <a href="https://aistudio.google.com/app">Google AI Studio</a> to prototype and test prompt chains before deploying them to production via custom Node.js packages connected to their mobile backend.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              Prior to using Gemini models, tasks involving multimodal data interpretation often required complex custom logic or the chaining of disparate models. By adopting <b>Gemini 2.5 Flash Image</b>, HubX consolidated these tasks into a single, coherent modeling framework, reducing architectural complexity while improving inference speed.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>What\u2019s next</h2>"},body:'<p>\n              Following the successful integration of the Gemini API, HubX observed an increase in user engagement, as indicated by higher save and like rates on generated content. Looking ahead, they plan to evolve ReShoot from a single-purpose tool into a comprehensive platform for native, seamless photo editing.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              HubX\u2019s implementation demonstrates how developers can leverage the speed and native multimodal capabilities of the Gemini API to build intuitive, high-performance applications that meet the demands of mobile users.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              To start building with Gemini models, read our <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/image-generation">image generation documentation</a>.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"related_cases",content:{qf:["vela","joltai","optimalai"]}}]},{title:"Cartwheel",We:"Beyond text prompts: how Cartwheel built pose-faithful 3D generation with Gemini Flash 2.5",slug:"cartwheel-2",Af:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-2.5-flash-image",thumbnail:{url:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/Cartwheel-1_thumbnail.jpg",alt:"Cartwheel showcase preview"},te:["Gemini 2.5 Flash Image"],modules:[{type:"hero",content:{date:"NOV 3, 2025",headline:"Beyond text prompts: how Cartwheel built pose-faithful 3D generation with Gemini Flash 2.5",
Ce:[{name:"Vishal Dharmadhikari",role:"Product Solutions Engineer"},{name:"Jonathan Jarvis",role:"Co-founder & CTO"},{name:"Andrew Carr",role:"Co-founder & Chief Scientist"}],thumbnail:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/Cartwheel-1_hero.jpg",type:"image",alt:"Cartwheel showcase hero"}}},{type:"cta",content:{link:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-2.5-flash-image"}},{type:"text",content:{body:'\n            <p>\n              Generative models have created new possibilities for artists and designers. However, for professional creators, translating a specific creative vision into a generated image remains a significant challenge. Text-only prompting can often feel like a "slot machine," making it difficult to achieve precise control over a character\'s pose, camera angle, and composition.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              <a href="https://getcartwheel.com/home">Cartwheel</a>, a platform for 3D AI-native game and media creation, is addressing this problem by building a novel solution on top of Google\'s advanced models, in this case Gemini 2.5 Flash Image Nano Banana. Their "Pose Mode" feature within Cartwheel Studio moves beyond simple text-to-image generation by incorporating 3D-native controls, giving creators direct, iterative control over their output.\n            </p>\n            '}},
{type:"images",content:{items:[{image:{src:"https://ai.google.dev/static/showcase/cartwheel-2/images/cartwheel_pose_04.jpg",alt:"Cartwheel Pose"}}]}},{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>The challenge: bridging the gap between intent and output</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              In professional creative workflows, precision is essential. An artist, advertiser, or game designer often needs to create a character in a specific pose or from a specific angle to fit a storyboard or campaign brief.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              "At a high level, image generators have been hard to control," said Jonathan Jarvis, co-founder of Cartwheel. "It\'s hard to achieve a vision that you actually have. We\'ve always wanted to let you just go in and directly manipulate the character."\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              This requirement for direct manipulation led Cartwheel to develop a multimodal pipeline that integrates 3D posing, text prompting, and multiple AI models to work in concert.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              The solution: a multi-model pipeline for pose-faithful generation\n              Instead of relying solely on text, Cartwheel\'s Pose Mode presents the user with a 3D mannequin. The user can directly click and drag the mannequin\'s limbs to create a specific pose and adjust the virtual camera to any angle. This 3D scene then becomes a primary input for the generative process.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              The technical workflow is as follows:\n            </p>\n            <ol>\n              <li><b>Pose labeling with Gemini 2.5 Flash.</b> First, a screenshot of the posed 3D mannequin is sent to Gemini 2.5 Flash. Cartwheel uses 2.5 Flash for this step, as its speed is ideal for the low-latency requirement of a real-time creative tool. The model\'s task is to return a simple text label describing the pose, such as "a character in a jumping pose" or "a character saluting."</li>\n              <li><b>Multimodal prompt assembly.</b> This 2.5 Flash-generated pose label is then automatically combined with the user\'s own descriptive text prompt (e.g., "a robot in a field of flowers").</li>\n              <li><b>Conditioned image generation.</b> Finally, this combined text prompt is sent to a high-fidelity, pose-faithful image model, Gemini 2.5 Flash Image, along with the original screenshot of the 3D pose. This multimodal prompt\u2014which includes both the image of the pose and the detailed text description\u2014conditions Gemini 2.5 Flash Image to generate an image that strictly adheres to the pose and camera angle, while applying the artistic style, character, and scene details from the text.</li>\n            </ol>\n            <p>\n              This chaining of models\u2014using 2.5 Flash for visual analysis and labeling, and 2.5 Flash Image for final, conditioned rendering\u2014allows Cartwheel to offer a unique workflow that combines the intuitive control of 3D software with the creative power of generative AI.\n              The results: unlocking character consistency from any angle\n              This approach has proven effective at generating images that were previously difficult to create. "Rendering characters from any angle but the front did not work in any other model," noted Andrew Carr, co-founder of Cartwheel. "As soon as you rotated the camera, it fell apart."\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              Because most image models are trained on data that overwhelmingly features characters from the front, they struggle to create less common compositions, such as high-angle shots or views from behind. By providing the pose as a direct visual input, Cartwheel\'s tool bypasses this training data bias, allowing an artist to generate consistent characters from any angle they choose.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              This workflow significantly accelerates the creative process. A task that might have previously required hours of iterative prompting or manual compositing by a 3D artist can now be accomplished in seconds.\n            </p>\n          '}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>What's next: from static images to generative video</h2>"},body:"\n            <p>\n              Cartwheel is already planning the next steps for this technology. The team is experimenting with integrating a library of 150,000 pre-categorized poses that users can search and refine, further speeding up the workflow.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              The long-term vision is to extend this pose-to-pixel pipeline into motion. The same 3D pose and rendered image could serve as the start frame for a video-to-video model, such as Veo. This would allow a creator to pose a character, render it in any style, and then animate it using a text prompt, creating a seamless workflow from 3D posing to a final, stylized animation.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              By building on top of multimodal models like those in the Gemini family, Cartwheel is demonstrating how developers can create sophisticated tools that provide artists with the control and consistency they need, moving generative AI from a tool of chance to one of precise creative intent.\n            </p>\n          "}},
{type:"related_cases",content:{qf:["volley-2","spline","promisestudios"]}}]},{title:"Pascal AI",We:"Pascal AI builds a multimodal parsing layer that processes diverse document sources and transforms intricate graphs and tables into structured data, circumventing the limitations of other OCR tools.",slug:"pascalai",Af:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-pro-latest",thumbnail:{url:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/Pascal_AI_thumbnail.jpg",alt:"Pascal AI showcase preview"},
te:["Gemini 2.5 Pro"],modules:[{type:"hero",content:{date:"NOV 3, 2024",headline:"Building a high-accuracy financial document intelligence system with Gemini 2.5 Pro",wr:"Pascal AI builds a multimodal parsing layer that processes diverse document sources and transforms intricate graphs and tables into structured data, circumventing the limitations of other OCR tools.",Ce:[{name:"Mithun Madhusudan",role:"Founder"},{name:"Vishal Dharmadhikari",role:"Product Solutions Engineer"}],thumbnail:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/Pascal_AI_hero.jpg",
type:"image",alt:"Pascal AI showcase hero"}}},{type:"stats",content:{stats:[{value:"100%",description:"Accuracy identifying elements"},{value:"96%",description:"Fidelity to source text"},{value:"2x",description:"Higher accuracy than next-best model"}]}},{type:"cta",content:{link:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-pro-latest"}},{type:"text",content:{body:'<p>\n              <a href="https://www.pascalailabs.com/">Pascal AI</a> is an AI-native operating system designed for investment funds, operating at an institutional scale to process millions of pages of filings, memos, and models. Their mission is to turn a firm\u2019s internal and external data into an AI-powered advantage, helping analysts and CIOs make faster, data-driven decisions.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              To build the knowledge graph that powers their agentic workflows, Pascal AI needed a document intelligence system capable of converting diverse, complex financial documents into structured text with exceptional accuracy.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>The challenge of parsing complex financial data</h2>"},body:"<p>\n              Financial documents present unique, stubborn challenges for programmatic parsing. Prior to integrating the Gemini API, the Pascal AI team tested various OCR tools and large language models, encountering persistent technical hurdles:\n            </p>\n            <ul>\n                <li>\n                <b>Complex visual data:</b> Extracting accurate data from multi-axis charts and trend graphs is non-trivial. Other models frequently hallucinated values not present in the original visuals, creating unacceptable reliability issues.\n                </li>\n                <li>\n                <b>Intricate table structures:</b> Financial statements often feature merged cells and span multiple pages both horizontally and vertically. Standard extraction libraries often failed to preserve this structure, losing critical context such as currency units or time periods.\n                </li>\n                <li>\n                <b>Varied document quality:</b> Data sources range from digital-native filings to low-resolution, scanned PDFs, making rigid parsing logic brittle.\n                </li>\n            </ul>\n            <p>\n              Pascal AI required a parsing layer that could handle this complexity without hallucination.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Achieving 2x greater accuracy with Gemini 1.5 Pro</h2>"},body:"<p>\n              To overcome these challenges, Pascal AI integrated <b>Gemini 1.5 Pro</b> via LangChain as the core of their document intelligence stack.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              According to Kanav Anand, AI Lead at Pascal AI, the model\u2019s multimodal reasoning significantly boosted accuracy. Unlike previous solutions, <b>Gemini 1.5 Pro</b> minimizes hallucinations and accurately transforms complex graphs and charts into structured markdown tables, preserving vital financial context.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              To measure success, Pascal AI utilizes an internal evaluation set, tracking <b>edit distance error-rate</b> to determine how close the parsed output is to the original text. <b>Gemini 1.5 Pro</b> achieved a low <b>4% edit distance error rate</b>, performing <b>2x more accurately</b> than the next best model tested. Furthermore, the model achieved <b>100% element-wise accuracy</b>, correctly identifying structural components like tables, paragraphs, and headers.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Simplifying parsing logic with prompt engineering</h2>"},body:'<p>\n              Beyond raw accuracy, the Gemini API improved development velocity. By solving complex document intelligence problems primarily through prompt engineering rather than brittle custom logic, the team can iterate quickly to support new document types as they become available.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              Looking ahead, Pascal AI aims to push towards near 100% parsing accuracy by experimenting with advanced methods, including model orchestration and fine-tuning for domain-specific financial reporting.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              To start building with Gemini models, read our <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models">API documentation</a>.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"related_cases",content:{qf:["bug0","harvey","calcam"]}}]},{title:"Raindrop",We:"Raindrop enables engineering teams to identify agent failures and resolve issues across millions of daily events by using Gemini 2.5 Flash for categorization and query rewriting in its Deep Search tool.",slug:"raindrop",Af:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-flash-latest",thumbnail:{url:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/Raindrop_thumbnail.jpg",alt:"Raindrop showcase preview"},
te:["Gemini 2.5 Flash"],modules:[{type:"hero",content:{date:"OCT 27, 2025",headline:"Raindrop monitors AI agent performance at scale using Gemini 2.5 Flash",wr:"Raindrop enables engineering teams to identify agent failures and resolve issues across millions of daily events by using Gemini 2.5 Flash for categorization and query rewriting in its Deep Search tool.",Ce:[{name:"Alexis Gauba",role:"Co-Founder"},{name:"Ben Hylak",role:"Co-Founder"},{name:"Vishal Dharmadhikari",role:"Product Solutions Engineer"}],
thumbnail:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/Raindrop_hero.jpg",type:"image",alt:"Raindrop showcase hero"}}},{type:"stats",content:{stats:[{value:"90%",description:"Reduction in costs"},{value:"~98%",description:"Reduction in search time"}]}},{type:"cta",content:{link:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-flash-latest"}},{type:"text",content:{body:'\n            <p>\n              AI agents present unique monitoring challenges compared to traditional software. Failures in AI systems are often "silent," meaning they may not produce standard exceptions or errors, which makes issue detection more difficult for engineering teams. Traditional debugging methods, such as sifting through logs or relying on pre-production evaluations, may fail to capture real-world performance issues.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              <a href="https://www.raindrop.ai/">Raindrop</a> provides a monitoring platform specifically designed for AI agents in production. It helps engineering teams identify complex issues like tool call failures and user frustration by processing massive streams of user interactions. To power its monitoring pipeline efficiently, Raindrop uses Gemini 2.5 Flash for categorization, summarization, and search re-ranking.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Enabling real-time monitoring at scale</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              Raindrop\'s platform processes tens of millions of events daily. A primary challenge for Raindrop is enabling engineering teams to query and classify issues across these vast datasets in near real-time. When a user defines a new issue to monitor, Raindrop\u2019s system must rapidly interpret the user\'s intent and analyze event streams to find matches.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              This high-throughput processing requires models that offer extremely low latency and high cost-efficiency. Raindrop needed a solution to power its core "semantic monitoring" pipeline and new features like Deep Search\u2014a tool for researching production AI data\u2014without incurring prohibitive costs or slow response times that would diminish the user experience.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              "We needed a model that could quickly process these initial events at a reasonable cost," said Ben Hylak, Co-Founder and CTO of Raindrop. "Gemini 2.5 Flash\u2019s low latency and intelligence enables our Deep Search product which would otherwise be unusable\u2014too slow and too expensive with other models."\n            </p>'}},
{type:"video",content:{video:{title:"Raindrop\u2019s deep search pipeline in action",sources:[{url:"https://ai.google.dev/static/showcase/raindrop/videos/deepsearch_searching.mp4",type:"video/mp4"}]}}},{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Implementing Gemini 2.5 Flash for speed and structured outputs</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              Raindrop integrated Gemini 2.5 Flash to manage categorization and query re-writing. The implementation was streamlined using the Vercel AI SDK, allowing Raindrop to integrate the models quickly.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              Raindrop leverages Gemini 2.5 Flash for several key functions:\n            </p>\n            <ul>\n              <li>\n                <b>Query expansion and re-writing:</b> In the Deep Search pipeline, Gemini 2.5 Flash is leveraged to rewrite user queries to optimize results, improving search relevance across millions of events.\n              </li>\n              <li>\n                <b>Structured outputs:</b> Raindrop utilizes tool calling and structured outputs to ensure more accurate results from model interactions. This reliability is critical for debugging and providing accurate reasoning traces to users.\n              </li>\n            </ul>\n            <p>\n              Before adopting Gemini 2.5 Flash, Raindrop evaluated other small models but found the cost-to-performance ratio unfavorable. "Other models were either too expensive, too slow, not intelligent enough, or did not produce reliable structured outputs.," Hylak noted. "The intelligence-to-cost ratio only made sense with Gemini 2.5 Flash."\n            </p>'}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Reducing search times and cutting costs by 90%</h2>"},body:"\n            <p>\n              By switching to the Gemini 2.5 Flash model, Raindrop achieved significant performance and efficiency gains.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              Key results include:\n            </p>\n            <ul>\n              <li>\n                <b>Search times reduced</b> from hours to often under a minute\n              </li>\n              <li>\n                <b>Costs cut</b> by more than 90%\n              </li>\n              <li>\n                <b>Increased reliability</b> across both evaluations and production monitoring\n              </li>\n            </ul>\n            <p>\n              Raindrop uses the Gemini API\u2019s support for structured outputs and tool calls within their Deep Search pipeline. This allows them to get accurate results and view reasoning traces for debugging, which is critical for maintaining a reliable system. The initial integration was completed in minutes using the Vercel AI SDK.</p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Building the future of agent observability</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              Raindrop is continuing to build out its agent-native monitoring platform with features like complete tracing and the automatic detection of tool-call issues. They believe that as AI models become faster and more reliable, agents will be able to handle increasingly complex tasks.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              "Developers should take advantage of Gemini 2.5 Flash\u2019s reliable structured outputs and pricing model to enable use cases that they may have previously thought were prohibitively expensive," Hylak advised. "Gemini 2.5 Flash can likely change the course of your product development by letting you give intelligent experiences to your users that actually work with your pricing model."\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              To start building your own applications, explore the capabilities of Gemini models in our  <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models">API documentation</a>.\n            </p>\n            '}},
{type:"related_cases",content:{qf:["bug0","firecrawl","pascalai"]}}]},{title:"Bug0",We:"Bug0's AI QA platform uses Gemini 2.5 Pro to automate testing, generate, and auto-heal tests. It cuts manual debugging by 60% and accurately summarizes test failures.",slug:"bug0",Af:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-pro-latest",thumbnail:{url:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/Bug0_thumbnail.jpg",alt:"Bug0 showcase preview"},te:["Gemini 2.5 Pro"],modules:[{type:"hero",content:{date:"OCT 20, 2025",
headline:"Bug0 reduces manual test debugging by 60% with Gemini 2.5 Pro",Ce:[{name:"Sandeep Panda",role:"co-founder & CTO of Bug0"},{name:"Vishal Dharmadhikari",role:"Product Solutions Engineer"}],thumbnail:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/Bug0_hero.jpg",type:"image",alt:"Bug0 showcase hero"}}},{type:"cta",content:{link:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-pro-latest"}},{type:"text",content:{body:'\n            <p>\n              Traditional software quality assurance (QA) often relies on brittle, selector-based tests that break when user interfaces change. Debugging these failures typically requires engineers to manually review test logs and recordings, a time-consuming process that slows development velocity.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              <a href="https://bug0.com/">Bug0</a>, an AI-powered QA platform, automates browser and mobile testing for engineering teams. Their platform is designed to generate, maintain, and auto-heal tests at scale, reducing the friction associated with traditional QA.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              To improve test reliability and automate the debugging process, Bug0 uses the multimodal reasoning capabilities of Gemini 2.5 Pro to analyze test recordings, validate outcomes, and automatically determine the root cause of failures.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Automating QA analysis with multimodal reasoning</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              Bug0 sought to reduce reliance on traditional assertion frameworks, such as Playwright, which depend on specific code selectors that frequently become outdated. They also needed a scalable way to analyze test outcomes without manual intervention.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              "Watching full test recordings to identify the root cause of a failure was time consuming, and maintaining complex selectors or flaky assertions slowed us down," said Sandeep Panda, Co-founder and CTO of Bug0. "We needed a way to summarize test intent and outcomes automatically using AI."\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              Bug0 selected Gemini 2.5 Pro specifically for its advanced multimodal capabilities, particularly its ability to interpret video.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              They implemented Gemini 2.5 Pro for two primary functions:\n            </p>\n            <ul>\n              <li>\n                <b>AI assertion engine:</b> The engine evaluates whether a test objective was met based on visual or structural evidence, such as video recordings, page screenshots, or accessibility snapshots. This replaces fragile code locators with robust, AI-powered assertions.                </li>\n              <li>\n                <b>Failure summarization:</b> An AI agent analyzes video recordings of failed tests and summarizes the root cause (e.g., a missing button or an incorrect redirect), reducing the need for engineers to review the footage manually.\n              </li>\n            </ul>'}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Implementing video-based assertions and summaries</h2>"},body:"\n            <p>\n              Bug0 integrated Gemini 2.5 Pro using the Google Gen AI SDK in Node.js. The initial integration, including prompt experimentation and tuning, took approximately three days.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              Their AI assertion engine combines the actions of their testing framework with the evaluation capabilities of Gemini 2.5 Pro. The framework executes the test steps, and Gemini 2.5 Pro evaluates the resulting output.\n           </p>"}},
{type:"images",content:{items:[{image:{src:"https://ai.google.dev/static/showcase/bug0/images/DashboardScreenshot.jpg",alt:"Bug0 dashboard test run details"}}]}},{type:"text",content:{body:'\n            <p>\n               "In our assertion engine, we combine Gemini 2.5 Pro with Playwright. Playwright performs steps. Gemini 2.5 Pro evaluates the visual output and confirms whether the expected outcome was met," Panda explained. "This allows us to skip writing fragile locators or hard-coded expectations and rely on natural-language assertions powered by Gemini 2.5 Pro."\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              For failure summaries, Bug0 uses a specialized prompt format that includes the video recording, failure logs, and expected behaviors. Gemini 2.5 Pro processes this input to generate human-readable summaries explaining why the test failed. The accuracy of Gemini 2.5 Pro was essential for these critical QA tasks.\n           </p>'}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Reducing manual test review by 60%</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              The integration of Gemini 2.5 Pro significantly improved Bug0\'s debugging workflows and the overall reliability of their platform. By replacing manual debugging and assertion writing with AI-driven workflows, Bug0 accelerated development velocity for its customers.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              Key results include:\n            </p>\n            <ul>\n              <li>\n                <b>60% reduction</b> in the number of test failure videos that engineers need to manually watch\n              </li>\n              <li>\n                <b>Over 70%</b> of test failures are now successfully auto-summarized with accurate root cause explanations\n              </li>\n              <li>\n                A significant drop in assertion flakiness compared to traditional selector-based methods\n              </li>\n            </ul>\n            <p>\n              "Gemini 2.5 Pro accelerated our velocity," Panda said. "It elevated our core product experience by turning test review from a bottleneck into a fast-feedback loop."\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              Bug0 is now developing an AI test authoring feature. Users will be able to submit a video of a user flow, and Bug0 will use Gemini 2.5 Pro to analyze the video and automatically generate the corresponding test script and assertions.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              To start building your own applications, explore the multimodal capabilities of Gemini models in our <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models">API documentation</a>.\n            </p>'}}]},
{title:"Firecrawl",We:"Firecrawl integrates complex reasoning into its platform for SmartScrape, a tool for context-aware extraction, and FIRE-1, an agent framework that interprets user goals and invokes functions for handling complex web navigation tasks.",slug:"firecrawl",Af:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-pro-latest",thumbnail:{url:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/Firecrawl_thumbnail.jpg",alt:"Firecrawl showcase preview"},te:["Gemini 2.5 Pro"],modules:[{type:"hero",
content:{date:"OCT 20, 2025",headline:"Firecrawl uses Gemini 2.5 Pro to structure web data for AI applications",wr:"Firecrawl integrates complex reasoning into its platform for SmartScrape, a tool for context-aware extraction, and FIRE-1, an agent framework that interprets user goals and invokes functions for handling complex web navigation tasks.",Ce:[{name:"Eric Ciarla",role:"Co-Founder"},{name:"Vishal Dharmadhikari",role:"Product Solutions Engineer"}],thumbnail:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/Firecrawl_hero.jpg",
type:"image",alt:"Firecrawl showcase hero"}}},{type:"stats",content:{stats:[{value:"98%",description:"accuracy vs. ~80% in next-best model"}]}},{type:"cta",content:{link:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-pro-latest"}},{type:"text",content:{body:'\n            <p>\n              AI applications, such as retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) systems and autonomous agents, increasingly require access to live, real-world information from the web. However, web content is often unstructured, dynamic, and inconsistent, making reliable data extraction a significant challenge for developers.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              <a href="https://www.firecrawl.dev/">Firecrawl</a>, an AI-first web data platform, provides APIs that enable developers and AI systems to programmatically find, fetch, parse, and structure web data at scale. They abstract the complexity of traditional web scraping, transforming unstructured web content into clean, usable data.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              To achieve this, Firecrawl uses Gemini 2.5 Pro to power its core extraction engine. Gemini models provide the advanced language understanding and reasoning capabilities necessary to accurately parse diverse and irregular web content.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Turning the unstructured web into usable data</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              Firecrawl aims to make the entire web accessible for AI systems. Traditional rule-based web scraping methods are often brittle and require constant maintenance because website structures change frequently. Firecrawl needed a solution capable of understanding context and extracting data reliably, even from highly variable sources.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              Firecrawl developed two core products using Gemini 2.5 Pro:\n            </p>\n            <ul>\n              <li>\n                <b>SmartScrape:</b> An extraction tool that uses Gemini 2.5 Pro\u2019s language understanding and reasoning capabilities to transform raw HTML into structured outputs, such as JSON or key-value pairs. It performs context-aware extraction, understanding the meaning of data relative to user-specified goals, rather than just its location on a page.\n              </li>\n              <li>\n                <b>FIRE-1:</b> An experimental agent framework that uses Gemini 2.5 Pro to interpret user intent, navigate web content, and generate outputs based on live web data.\n              </li>\n            </ul>\n            <p>\n              Before adopting Gemini 2.5 Pro, Firecrawl evaluated several leading models. They found that other models struggled to handle the complexity and variability of real-world web content at production scale.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              "Gemini 2.5 Pro made the entire project feasible," said Eric Ciarla, Co-founder of Firecrawl. "Before using Gemini 2.5 Pro, the models we tested couldn\u2019t reliably handle the level of complexity required to extract and reason over real-world web content. Gemini 2.5 Pro\u2019s reasoning capabilities, accuracy, and stability enabled us to move forward with confidence."\n            </p>'}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Implementing Gemini 2.5 Pro with tool calling</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              Firecrawl integrated Gemini 2.5 Pro into their products in approximately one week. They leverage the model\u2019s reasoning and tool calling capabilities within their agent architecture.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              In the FIRE-1 agent framework, the model operates within an agent loop that combines Gemini 2.5 Pro\u2019s reasoning with deterministic control flows. The process works as follows:\n            </p>\n            <ul>\n              <li>\n                <b>Input:</b> The agent receives the webpage Document Object Model (DOM) and a defined user goal (e.g., "get me all the pages on this website").\n              </li>\n              <li>\n                <b>Reasoning:</b> Gemini 2.5 Pro analyzes the inputs and determines the necessary actions.\n              </li>\n              <li>\n                <b>Execution:</b> The model executes these actions via tool calling (function calls). For navigation tasks, the agent might autonomously invoke functions like click(next_page) to retrieve the required data.\n              </li>\n            </ul>\n            <p>\n              This approach allows Firecrawl to handle complex web navigation and extraction tasks that require both flexibility and predictability.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Achieving 98% extraction accuracy</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              In internal benchmarks comparing extraction accuracy and complex web parsing, Gemini 2.5 Pro significantly outperformed other models Firecrawl evaluated.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              Gemini 2.5 Pro achieved 98% accuracy in Firecrawl\'s internal evaluations. The next-best model tested reached approximately 80% accuracy. This performance increase translated directly into higher-quality extraction outputs and more reliable agent behavior in production workloads.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              "In our internal testing, Gemini 2.5 Pro consistently outperformed the alternatives across every key dimension for our use case: extraction accuracy, complex reasoning, latency, and overall throughput," Ciarla noted.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Building the future of web interaction</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              Gemini models are now a foundational component of Firecrawl\u2019s AI infrastructure, enabling them to provide reliable web data pipelines for AI products.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              Firecrawl is currently evaluating Gemini 2.5 Flash for use cases requiring ultra-low latency, where real-time agentic interaction is critical. As the Gemini model family evolves, Firecrawl plans to integrate new capabilities to further improve how AI agents interact with real-world web data.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              To start building your own applications, explore the capabilities of Gemini models in our <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models">API documentation</a>.\n            </p>\n            '}}]},
{title:"Passionfroot",We:"Passionfroot uses AI to help brands run creator marketing campaigns by automating manual tasks and providing tools for seamless collaboration.",slug:"passionfroot",Af:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-flash-latest",thumbnail:{url:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/Passionfroot_thumbnail.jpg",alt:"Passionfroot showcase preview"},te:["Gemini 2.5 Flash"],modules:[{type:"hero",content:{date:"AUG 29, 2025",headline:"Passionfroot scales creator marketing ~5x faster using Gemini 2.5 Flash",
Ce:[{name:"Vishal Dharmadhikari",role:"Product Solutions Engineer"},{name:"Lorenzo De Nobili",role:"Co-Founder and CTO"}],thumbnail:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/Passionfroot_hero.jpg",type:"image",alt:"Passionfroot showcase hero"}}},{type:"cta",content:{link:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-flash-latest"}},{type:"text",content:{body:"\n            <p>\n              Creator marketing in sectors like B2B SaaS, AI, and fintech is effective but difficult to scale. Unlike performance marketing, managing creator partnerships often involves manual processes and hands-on relationship management.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              Passionfroot, a creator marketplace connecting brands with creators in emerging tech industries, addresses this complexity by streamlining discovery, outreach, booking, payments and results reporting. To help marketers design and launch effective creator marketing campaigns, Passionfroot developed an AI Campaign Strategist powered by Gemini 2.5 Flash.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Automating campaign strategy with an AI agent</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              Marketers often face a "blank page problem" when initiating creator campaigns: identifying suitable creators, defining ad types, and allocating budgets. Passionfroot developed its AI Campaign Strategist to automate this process and help marketers scale their efforts.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              The AI agent uses Gemini models to generate tailored creator marketing campaigns based on specific audience and growth targets. It provides recommendations on creators, budget allocation, content placements and estimates expected CPM and engagement.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              Passionfroot needed a model capable of understanding the nuances of effective creator marketing to guide the agent\'s strategy.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Optimizing for latency and instruction following with Gemini 2.5 Flash</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              When developing the Strategist, Passionfroot required a model that offered low latency, precise instruction following, and cost-effective performance. Their workflow involves multiple sequential prompts to fulfill a single user request, making speed critical.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              The team evaluated several advanced models, including Gemini 2.5 Pro. After prompt engineering, they determined that Gemini 2.5 Flash provided exceptional results while significantly reducing latency.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              "There is no other model that gets even close to the intelligence/latency of Gemini 2.5 Flash," said Lorenzo De Nobili, Co-Founder and CTO of Passionfroot.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              The implementation uses the Vercel AI SDK and relies heavily on structured output (generateObject). Instead of a chat-based interface, Gemini\u2019s structured responses directly control the application\u2019s user interface.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              The AI Campaign Strategist workflow involves three key steps:\n            </p>\n            <ul>\n              <li><b>Strategy generation:</b> Gemini identifies ideal channels, placement types, and budget allocations based on the marketer\u2019s input.</li>\n              <li><b>Creator matching:</b> Agentic retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) retrieves and evaluates the most relevant creators based on topical relevance.</li>\n              <li><b>Inventory analysis:</b> The inventory of selected creators is analyzed, and the AI agent selects the top-performing product based on expected ROI.</li>\n            </ul>'}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Launching creator partnerships ~5x faster</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              The implementation of the Gemini-powered AI Campaign Strategist has delivered measurable improvements in efficiency and growth for Passionfroot\u2019s customers.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              Brands using the AI strategist launch partnerships ~5x faster than brands who manage partnerships manually. This reduction in friction has enabled Passionfroot\u2019s marketing partners to triple their growth within the first three months of running creator marketing on the platform.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              "Our campaign strategist would have simply not been possible without AI," De Nobili noted. "It\u2019s incredible to be able to teach a computer about creator marketing so that it can act as a creator marketing expert to provide 1-1 advice to our users."\n            </p>'}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Future development</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              Passionfroot plans to enhance the AI Campaign Strategist by performing deeper analysis of creator content, including assessing tone of voice and delivery style. They are also integrating ROI data from collaborations to further refine the agent\u2019s recommendations. By combining Gemini\u2019s capabilities with proprietary data, Passionfroot aims to provide sophisticated, data-driven insights for creator marketing.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              To explore how Gemini models can streamline your workflows, review our <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs">API documentation</a>.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              <i>Performance metrics were provided by developers and not independently confirmed by Google. </i>\n            </p>'}},
