modules:[{type:"hero",content:{date:"APRIL 9, 2025",headline:"Fast, accurate nutritional analysis with CalCam and Gemini 2.0 Flash",Ce:[{name:"Vishal Dharmadhikari",role:"Product Solutions Engineer"},{name:"Queena Qiu",role:"Co-founder of Polyverse"}],thumbnail:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/Calcam_hero.jpg",type:"image",alt:"AgentOps showcase hero"}}},{type:"cta",content:{link:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-flash-latest"}},{type:"text",content:{body:"\n            <p>\n              The Gemini API enables developers to create complex applications that feel simple and intuitive for end users. App developer Polyverse helps users track their nutrition through the CalCam app, which uses AI to analyze images for caloric intake and power engaging features such as nutrition posters and meal ratings. By using the Gemini API, Polyverse improved response times, increased user satisfaction ratings by 20%, and enhanced internal workflows with streamlined tooling.\n            </p>"}},
{type:"images",content:{items:[{image:{src:"https://ai.google.dev/static/images/showcase/calcam/calcam-gemini-app.png",alt:"The CalCam app analyzes the user\u2019s photo of a meal, calculates macronutrients, and tracks caloric intake."}}]}},{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Enhanced precision for better health insights</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              CalCam users track their nutrition by providing photos of their meals for analysis. After processing the photo, <a href="https://deepmind.google/technologies/gemini/flash/">Gemini 2.0 Flash</a> generates structured JSON outputs that integrate with CalCam\u2019s workflow to calculate dish ingredients, weights, and macronutrient information. These outputs are further assessed against nutritional knowledge and logic to enhance the accuracy and consistency of the results.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"images",content:{items:[{image:{src:"https://ai.google.dev/static/images/showcase/calcam/calcam-gemini-data.png",alt:"CalCam users can provide corrections if needed, prompting the Gemini model to re-evaluate and generate a new, refined analysis."}}]}},{type:"text",content:{body:"\n            <p>\n              Integrating Gemini 2.0 Flash\u2019s abilities to pick up on subtle elements, such as sauces and seasonings, and refine analyses based on feedback, CalCam empowers users to track their meals with better precision and make informed decisions about their diet and health.</p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Streamlined app development with the help of Google AI Studio</h2>"},body:'\n            <p>\n              Polyverse highlights the ease of customizing Gemini models as critical to accelerating the development process. The structured output visual editor in <a href="https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_data">Google AI Studio</a> allowed non-programmers on the CalCam team to contribute to structuring and editing outputs, reducing the reliance on coding expertise.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"images",content:{items:[{image:{src:"https://ai.google.dev/static/images/showcase/calcam/google-ai-studio-gemini-nutrition-analysis.png",alt:"Google AI Studio\u2019s structured output editor can be used to specify the JSON schema for model responses."},legend:"Note: Data is an example schema for visualization purposes only and not representative of real app data."}]}},{type:"text",content:{body:'\n            <p>\n              In the future, Polyverse plans to develop even more interactive and personalized features, such as AI-driven recipes and coaching, to achieve CalCam\'s mission of making healthy living fun and accessible. By leveraging powerful multimodal reasoning and structured output tools in the <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs">Gemini API</a>, app functionality will continue to improve and make it even more valuable for health-conscious users.\n            </p>\n            <p>\n              Download <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.ai.calcam">CalCam</a> to start working towards your nutrition goals and explore image reasoning with Gemini 2.0 Flash in <a href="https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-flash-latest">Google AI Studio</a>.\n            </p>'}},
{type:"related_cases",content:{qf:["wolfgames","vela","langbase"]}}]},{title:"tldraw",We:"Prototyping a new natural language computing experience on an infinite canvas with Gemini 2.0",slug:"tldraw",Af:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-flash-latest",thumbnail:{url:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/TlDraw_thumbnail.jpg",alt:"tldraw showcase preview"},te:["Gemini 1.5 Flash","Gemini 2.0 Flash"],modules:[{type:"hero",content:{date:"DEC 11, 2024",headline:"Gemini powers tldraw's natural language computing experience",
Ce:[{name:"Vishal Dharmadhikari",role:"Product Solutions Engineer"},{name:"Steve Ruiz",role:"tldraw"}],thumbnail:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/TlDraw_hero.jpg",type:"image",alt:"Tldraw showcase hero"}}},{type:"cta",content:{link:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-flash-latest"}},{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Unlocking natural language interactions with the Gemini API</h2>"},body:'\n              <p>\n                The Gemini API empowers developers to seamlessly integrate advanced AI capabilities into their applications, unlocking new possibilities for user experience and functionality. This post highlights how tldraw leverages Gemini to build a revolutionary "natural language computing" experience within their new project, <a href="https://computer.tldraw.com/">computer</a>. This demonstrates the speed and ease with which startups can integrate powerful AI using the Gemini API and tldraw\u2019s <a href="https://tldraw.dev">canvas SDK</a>. The tldraw team is launching computer with <a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models/gemini#gemini-1.5-flash">Gemini 1.5 Flash</a> soon (<a href="https://computer.tldraw.com/">join the waitlist</a>) and is currently prototyping with <a href="http://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models/gemini#gemini-2.0-flash">Gemini 2.0</a> Flash for future iterations.\n              </p>'}},
{type:"video",content:{video:{title:"Animation showing a web comic called 18 Days being translated in Hindi using Gemini 2.0",sources:[{url:"https://ai.google.dev/static/images/showcase/tldraw/final.mp4",type:"video/mp4"}]}}},{type:"text",content:{body:"\n              <p>tldraw is using the Gemini API to bring the power of conversational AI to visual programming, allowing users to generate content and process information using natural language. This opens up exciting opportunities for more intuitive and efficient user experience around AI, pushing the boundaries of visual communication.</p>"}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>The vision behind computer</h2>"},body:'\n              <p>\n                tldraw, striving to make diagramming accessible and intuitive, envisioned a more natural way for users to interact with their canvas. Founder Steve Ruiz sought to leverage the power of tldraw\u2019s infinite canvas SDK to create a dynamic environment for working with generative AI. This vision led to the development of <a href="http://computer.tldraw.com">computer</a>, an experimental application where users create workflows from blocks of text, images, and instructions. When run, information flows from one component to the next, with the output of each generation serving as the input to the next, creating powerful processes that branch, loop, and iterate to produce outputs.\n              </p>'}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Building with Gemini 2.0: a deep dive into computer</h2>"},body:'\n              <p>\n                tldraw\u2019s computer is built upon a network of interconnected \u201ccomponents\u201d representing elements on the canvas (text boxes, images, audio clips, etc.). These components are linked by arrows, visualizing the flow of data and transformations. Each component has associated "procedures"\u2014sets of instructions executed based on inputs from connected components. A component can accept data from any number of other components and pass its output data to many other components\u2014including itself! This component-based architecture, combined with the power and speed of Gemini 2.0 Flash, allows for a fast and flexible system capable of handling diverse tasks.\n              </p>'}},
{type:"video",content:{video:{title:"Animation showing visual prompting with text and image generation in tldraw computer",sources:[{url:"https://ai.google.dev/static/images/showcase/tldraw/text-image-gen.mp4",type:"video/mp4"}],legend:"tldraw computer\u2019s AI visual programming with text gen using Gemini 2.0 and image generation with an image gen model"}}},{type:"text",content:{body:'\n              <p>\n                Here\'s how Gemini 2.0 Flash prototyping has powered the experience:\n              </p>\n              <ul>\n                <li><p><strong>Lightning-Fast procedure execution:</strong> Gemini 2.0 Flash executes procedures rapidly. For example, an "Instruction" component might contain "Write a short commercial." Within moments of being triggered, the component will have generated a re-usable script of steps that can turn any combination of inputs into a commercial script. The component will then use this script, together with its current inputs (e.g., a "Text" component with "New AI-powered smartgloves for cats"), to make a second prompt to the model for its final output. This output may be passed to another linked "Text" component for display, as well as other connected components, like "Speech" for text-to-speech, "Image" for visual generation, or other \u201cInstruction\u201d components for further transformation.</p></li>\n                <li><p><strong>Lots of context, many modes:</strong> The maximalist bent in tldraw\u2019s computer called for speed, capacity, and capability. With multiple components providing data for each generation, Gemini 2.0 Flash\u2019s large context window was critical for producing outputs that took all inputs into account, as was its support for images and files alongside written prompts.</p></li>\n                <li><p><strong>Structured data:</strong> The flow of data between components would not be possible without adherence to a single schema. The structured JSON output from Gemini 2.0 Flash ensures that each component in a workflow can recognize data of any type and produce its outputs in the same structure, preventing stalls, smoothing execution, and ensuring even large workflows will reliably complete.</p></li>\n                <li><p><strong>Dynamic procedure generation:</strong> Beyond executing predefined procedures, Gemini 2.0 Flash can generate procedures dynamically. A user could input "create a marketing campaign based on this product description," and Gemini 2.0 Flash would generate the necessary steps (procedures) and the required components, building a workflow on the canvas based on the user\'s high-level request. This dynamic generation unlocks tremendous potential for innovative user experiences and streamlined workflows.</p></li>\n              </ul>'}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>A quick win for innovation</h2>"},body:"\n              <p>\n                tldraw\u2019s quick implementation of computer highlights Gemini\u2019s value proposition for startups: rapid prototyping, enhanced user experience through intuitive natural language interfaces, and efficient structured data handling thanks to models like Gemini 2.0 Flash. This combination empowers small teams to create innovative, AI-powered features quickly and cost-effectively.\n              </p>"}},
{type:"quote",content:{quote:"We want to show that any team can build ambitious projects with tldraw\u2019s canvas SDK. Gemini Flash was a perfect engine for a fast, multi-modal, canvas-based workflow tool. With Gemini 2.0 and perhaps a better name, I\u2019m pretty sure we could pitch computer as its own startup tomorrow.",author:"\u2014 Steve Ruiz, Founder of tldraw"}},{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Empower your application with the Gemini API</h2>"},body:'\n              <p>\n                Inspired by tldraw\'s success? The Gemini API offers powerful models like Gemini 1.5 Pro, Gemini 1.5 Flash, and now Gemini 2.0 Flash as an experimental preview model to bring innovative AI features to your application. Explore  {<a href="https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs">Gemini API documentation</a> and empower your users with AI.\n              </p>\n              <p>\n                For creative professionals, developers, and teams of all kinds, tldraw offers a unique and powerful platform to bring ideas to life. <a href="https://computer.tldraw.com/">Join the computer waitlist</a>Experience the future of visual collaboration <a href="https://tldraw.dev/">today</a>.\n              </p>'}},
{type:"related_cases",content:{qf:["toonsutra-2","calcam","wolfgames"]}}]},{title:"Rooms",We:"Unlocking richer avatar interactions with Gemini 2.0 text and audio capabilities",slug:"rooms",Af:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-flash-latest",thumbnail:{url:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/Rooms_thumbnail.jpg",alt:"Rooms showcase preview"},te:["Gemini 2.0 Flash"],cCa:!0,modules:[{type:"hero",content:{date:"DEC 11, 2024",headline:"Rooms reimagines 3D spaces with interactive avatars using Gemini 2.0 Flash",
Ce:[{name:"Vishal Dharmadhikari",role:"Product Solutions Engineer"},{name:"Jason Toff",role:"Rooms"}],thumbnail:{src:"https://www.gstatic.com/aistudio/case_studies/Rooms_hero.jpg",type:"image",alt:"Rooms showcase hero"}}},{type:"cta",content:{link:"https://aistudio.google.com/prompts/new_chat?model=gemini-flash-latest"}},{type:"text",content:{body:'\n              <p>\n                <a href="http://rooms.xyz">Rooms</a>, an innovative platform where users create, play, and share interactive 3D spaces and games, is taking a significant step forward with the Gemini API. By integrating advanced text and new audio output capabilities of <a href="http://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models/gemini#gemini-2.0-flash">Gemini 2.0 Flash</a>, which is currently available in experimental preview only, Rooms is poised to unlock richer user interaction and creativity within its immersive 3D environments.\n              </p>'}},
{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Inside rooms: building the future of 3D interaction with Gemini 2.0 Flash</h2>"}}},{type:"images",content:{items:[{image:{src:"https://ai.google.dev/static/images/showcase/rooms/r01_2.jpg",alt:"Image with multiple room graphics in a honeycomb view"}}]}},{type:"text",content:{body:'\n              <p>\n                Rooms empowers users to build and explore a universe of user-generated 3D experiences, much like a digital equivalent of LEGO. Available on the web and mobile, Rooms provides intuitive building tools and social features that foster creativity and connection. Hundreds of thousands of users are already creating, sharing, and playing in this vibrant digital world.\n              </p>\n              <p>\n                "I have come to believe that creative expression isn\'t just a nicety, but rather a deep human need," says Jason Toff, the founder and CEO of Rooms. "The internet is evolving to be richer and more immersive, which will necessitate 3D objects. The creation of these objects will be democratized, allowing anyone to build and share their creations. 3D objects will come to life and be interactive, further blurring the lines between the digital and physical worlds, and Gen AI is a key part of this evolution."\n              </p>\n              <p>\n                Rooms is now prototyping with Gemini 2.0 Flash to unlock a new era of avatar interaction, transforming static avatars into dynamic characters capable of engaging in rich, natural conversations:\n              </p>\n              <ul>\n                <li><p><strong>Dynamic conversations:</strong> Gemini 2.0 Flash\'s new audio out capabilities allow for more fluid and engaging conversations between avatars. Imagine avatars responding to user prompts not just with text, but with expressive, lifelike voices generated in real-time.</p></li>\n                <li><p><strong>AI-Powered personalities:</strong> Beyond dynamic conversations, Rooms is using Gemini 2.0 Flash to imbue each avatar with unique personality traits, backstories, and even motivations. By feeding Gemini 2.0 Flash rich character profiles and contextual information, Rooms can generate avatars that behave and interact in diverse and engaging ways. This opens up exciting possibilities for role-playing, collaborative storytelling, and emergent gameplay.</p></li>\n              </ul>'}},
{type:"youtube_video",content:{video:{YG:"2qndbM4Bbjc"}}},{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Elevating the Rooms experience with Gemini 2.0 Flash</h2>"},body:"\n              <p>\n                Integrating Gemini 2.0 Flash promises to transform Rooms in several key ways:\n              </p>\n              <ul>\n                <li><p><strong>Deeper immersion:</strong> More realistic and responsive avatar interactions will create a deeper sense of presence and immersion within the 3D worlds.</p></li>\n                <li><p><strong>Richer engagement: </strong> Dynamic conversations and AI-powered personalities will foster more engaging and meaningful social connections between users.</p></li>\n                <li><p><strong>Limitless creativity:</strong> Users will be able to craft richer narratives and experiences, blurring the lines between gaming and social interaction.</p></li>\n                <li><p><strong>Interactive learning opportunities:</strong> Users can engage in interactive conversations with AI-powered historical figures, scientists, or literary characters, bringing learning to life in a whole new way.</p></li>\n              </ul>"}},
{type:"quote",content:{quote:"We're incredibly excited about the potential of Gemini 2.0 to enhance the Rooms experience. The ability to have dynamic, AI-powered conversations and interactions within our 3D spaces is a game-changer. It will unlock a new level of immersion, creativity, and connection for our users, and we can't wait to see what they create.",author:"\u2014 Jason Toff, CEO of Rooms"}},{type:"text",content:{header:{headline:"<h2>Future roadmap and vision</h2>"},body:"\n              <p>\n                Rooms is committed to pushing the boundaries of 3D interaction with a strong emphasis on responsible AI development. They envision a future where AI seamlessly blends with user creativity, fostering vibrant communities and boundless self-expression within their ever-expanding universe of 3D spaces.\n              </p>\n              <p>\n                Jason continues, \"We see a future where AI becomes an invisible but essential part of the 3D experience, enhancing creativity, immersion, and social connection. Imagine AI-powered characters that can safely engage in meaningful conversations, adapt to user behavior, and even co-create alongside users. This will open up endless possibilities for new forms of storytelling, gameplay, and virtual interactions, but it's crucial that these interactions are safe and inclusive. We're dedicated to responsible AI at Rooms.\u201d\n              </p>\n              <p>\n                With the Gemini API, Rooms is proving that advanced AI can be seamlessly integrated to create truly engaging and user-friendly 3D experiences. They're not just building a platform; they're demonstrating the power of AI to transform how we interact, create, and connect in digital worlds. Explore the <a href=\"http://ai.google.dev/gemini-api\">Gemini API</a> and discover its potential.\n              </p>"}},
